WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:01.100 --> 00:00:04.070
Even though I could not see
or hear anything,

00:00:04.103 --> 00:00:07.673
I could sense the world
losing patience with me.

00:00:07.706 --> 00:00:10.076
But still, I needed
to communicate.

00:00:10.109 --> 00:00:12.645 size:66% position:33%
So, did you guys want
to order?

00:00:12.678 --> 00:00:14.714 align:start size:91% position:9%
Or do you need
some more time?

00:00:14.747 --> 00:00:17.350
I tried everything I imagine
Helen must have tried --

00:00:17.383 --> 00:00:19.352
clapping,
charades-style clues...

00:00:19.385 --> 00:00:20.620 align:start size:63% position:38% line:85%
Tina: He has to pee.

00:00:19.385 --> 00:00:20.620
...guttural moaning.

00:00:20.653 --> 00:00:22.422
Surely,
one of these tools,

00:00:22.455 --> 00:00:24.590
commonly used by the disabled,
would do the trick.

00:00:24.623 --> 00:00:26.592 line:85%
[ Moans ]

00:00:24.623 --> 00:00:26.592
Lucille: Sounds like...

00:00:26.625 --> 00:00:28.394
Forrest: But on a day when
I wanted to be taken

00:00:28.427 --> 00:00:30.129
to see my ex-wife,

00:00:30.162 --> 00:00:32.165
I was instead
robbed of my shoes.

00:00:32.198 --> 00:00:33.399
[ Grunts ]

00:00:33.432 --> 00:00:35.101
On a day when
I wanted a light snack,

00:00:35.134 --> 00:00:36.836
I was instead
given a pen.

00:00:36.869 --> 00:00:39.572 align:start size:88% position:13%
[ Grunting ]

00:00:39.605 --> 00:00:42.408
On a day when I wanted to play
catch with my son, Eric,

00:00:42.441 --> 00:00:46.246
like I used to, I was instead
brought to a drugs party.

00:00:48.447 --> 00:00:49.749
And finally, on a day

00:00:49.782 --> 00:00:52.351
when I wanted to be taken
for a stroll outside,

00:00:52.384 --> 00:00:54.554
I was troublingly
brought to court,

00:00:54.587 --> 00:00:56.789
where I was facing
trial for murder.

00:00:56.822 --> 00:01:00.426
My caretakers had
failed me spectacularly.

00:01:00.459 --> 00:01:05.765
This was the worst possible time
to be deaf, dumb, and blind.

00:01:05.798 --> 00:01:07.600 align:start size:84% position:16% line:92%
[ Grunts ]

00:01:05.798 --> 00:01:07.600 align:start size:38% position:63%
Okay, right.

00:01:07.633 --> 00:01:09.268
Daisy: And what is your
relationship

00:01:09.301 --> 00:01:10.770
with your ex-husband?

00:01:10.803 --> 00:01:12.538
Forrest: I was unable to discuss
anything with my lawyer...

00:01:12.571 --> 00:01:13.840 align:start size:59% position:41%
He's my ex-husband.

00:01:13.873 --> 00:01:15.708
...who made
the questionable decision

00:01:15.741 --> 00:01:18.111
to call my ex-wife
as a character witness.

00:01:18.144 --> 00:01:20.213 size:66% position:33%
During the time
of your marriage,

00:01:20.246 --> 00:01:22.348 size:75% position:38%
did he bring you flowers

00:01:22.381 --> 00:01:25.218 align:start position:0%
or pay you compliments?

00:01:25.251 --> 00:01:27.487 line:85%
[ Forrest grunts ]

00:01:25.251 --> 00:01:27.487 align:start size:50% position:50%
Um, yes, he did.

00:01:27.520 --> 00:01:29.722 align:start position:0%
He did stuff like that?

00:01:29.755 --> 00:01:32.425 align:start size:38% position:63%
Yes.

00:01:32.458 --> 00:01:34.527 size:72% position:36%
Oh, well he sounds
like a really nice guy,

00:01:34.560 --> 00:01:35.828 align:start size:84% position:16%
doesn't he?

00:01:35.861 --> 00:01:37.864 size:66% position:33%
No further questions,
Your Honor!

00:01:37.897 --> 00:01:39.398
Forrest: While everyone
tried to ignore

00:01:39.431 --> 00:01:40.766
the presence
of a grunting visitor

00:01:40.799 --> 00:01:42.401
from the 19th century,

00:01:42.434 --> 00:01:43.870
Suzanne was asked if she thought

00:01:43.903 --> 00:01:45.838
I would commit murder
for the show.

00:01:45.871 --> 00:01:47.740
[ Grunts ]

00:01:47.773 --> 00:01:49.909 align:start size:50% position:50%
No, I don't.

00:01:49.942 --> 00:01:52.578 size:69% position:66%
He is overly
committed to his work,

00:01:52.611 --> 00:01:55.214 align:start size:50% position:50%
but he's not
so committed

00:01:55.247 --> 00:01:57.150 size:69% position:66%
that he would actually
kill somebody.

00:01:57.183 --> 00:01:59.485 line:85%
[ Forrest claps ]

00:01:57.183 --> 00:01:59.485 align:start size:44% position:56%
Oh, my God.

00:01:59.518 --> 00:02:01.254
And then, unbeknownst to me,

00:02:01.287 --> 00:02:03.890
my lawyer made an even
more perplexing decision.

00:02:03.923 --> 00:02:06.692 align:end position:100%
The defense would like
to call Forrest MacNeil.

00:02:06.725 --> 00:02:07.894 align:start size:94% position:6%
This way, ma'am.

00:02:07.927 --> 00:02:09.595 align:start size:50% position:50%
There we go.

00:02:09.628 --> 00:02:11.531
We had always planned
for Forrest MacNeil to testify.

00:02:11.564 --> 00:02:13.799 align:start size:38% position:63% line:92%
Down. Down!

00:02:11.564 --> 00:02:13.799 align:start position:0%
Daisy: Down!

00:02:13.832 --> 00:02:16.202
My attorney saw no reason
to change course,

00:02:16.235 --> 00:02:17.904
despite the fact
that Forrest MacNeil

00:02:17.937 --> 00:02:19.772
was now Helen Keller.

00:02:19.805 --> 00:02:21.707 align:end position:100%
Thank you for coming
to testify today, Mr. MacNeil.

00:02:21.740 --> 00:02:22.842 size:59% position:70%
I'm gonna cut
right to the chase.

00:02:22.875 --> 00:02:24.544
There is much Forrest MacNeil

00:02:24.577 --> 00:02:26.345
could have said
in his own defense.

00:02:26.378 --> 00:02:28.481 align:start size:53% position:47%
Is it true that
that guy, Ray,

00:02:28.514 --> 00:02:30.783 align:start size:59% position:41%
attacked you first?

00:02:30.816 --> 00:02:32.585 line:85%
Indeed it was true.

00:02:30.816 --> 00:02:32.585 align:start size:66% position:34%
Mr. MacNeil? Forrest?

00:02:32.618 --> 00:02:34.587
Ray, the man who was killed,

00:02:34.620 --> 00:02:36.289
was a violent sociopath.

00:02:36.322 --> 00:02:38.391
Oh. Oh. Oh. Oh, god.
Can I get out of here?

00:02:38.424 --> 00:02:39.926 align:start position:0% line:85%
Man: Oh, God!

00:02:38.424 --> 00:02:39.926
A man who would surely have been

00:02:39.959 --> 00:02:41.861
killed somebody someday.

00:02:41.894 --> 00:02:45.698 align:end position:100%
You did this in self-defense.
Is that true, Forrest?

00:02:45.731 --> 00:02:47.600 size:63% position:69%
Say, "Yes."
Just say, "Yes."

00:02:47.633 --> 00:02:49.435
The answer was yes.

00:02:49.468 --> 00:02:53.239
I had no doubt
Ray was beating me to death.

00:02:53.272 --> 00:02:56.909
You did this in self-defense.
Is that true?

00:02:56.942 --> 00:02:58.444 size:63% position:69%
All you have to do
is say, "Yes."

00:02:58.477 --> 00:03:00.313 align:start size:38% position:63% line:85%
Say, "Yes."

00:02:58.477 --> 00:03:00.313
[ Grunts ]

00:03:00.346 --> 00:03:03.249
But Helen could not answer,
even if she had known

00:03:03.282 --> 00:03:05.718
she was testifying
to save my life.

00:03:05.751 --> 00:03:06.852 size:63% position:69%
Okay, Forrest.
Come here.

00:03:06.885 --> 00:03:08.621
If only my attorney
had tried harder

00:03:08.654 --> 00:03:09.956
to remove my helmet,

00:03:09.989 --> 00:03:11.791
or had not called me
to stand at all.

00:03:11.824 --> 00:03:13.893 align:start size:53% position:47%
Oh! Oh, my God.

00:03:13.926 --> 00:03:15.795
Bailiff: Ma'am,
sit in your seat,

00:03:15.828 --> 00:03:17.563
or I will handcuff you
to this chair.

00:03:17.596 --> 00:03:21.334 align:end position:100%
Yeah. I think we got to
go back to the seats.

00:03:21.367 --> 00:03:23.536
Forrest: Being in constant need
of assistance made it clear

00:03:23.569 --> 00:03:26.005 line:85%
that in life...

00:03:23.569 --> 00:03:26.005 align:start size:91% position:9%
Be careful.

00:03:26.038 --> 00:03:28.674 size:84% position:42%
All right.
That is good enough for me.

00:03:28.707 --> 00:03:30.643
...we are surrounded by people

00:03:30.676 --> 00:03:33.679
who do not fully apply
themselves to their duties.

00:03:33.712 --> 00:03:36.549
As a result, I was not able
to exonerate myself.

00:03:36.582 --> 00:03:38.284
And "Review," once again,

00:03:38.317 --> 00:03:41.020
left my fate
in the hands of fate.

00:03:41.053 --> 00:03:43.789 align:start position:0%
Living as Helen Keller
was an isolating experience

00:03:43.822 --> 00:03:45.891 size:63% position:31%
that required trust,
perseverance,

00:03:45.924 --> 00:03:48.628 align:start position:0%
and a high tolerance
for minor abrasions.

00:03:48.661 --> 00:03:52.965
She was a remarkable woman and,
for a little while, so was I.

00:03:52.998 --> 00:03:57.003 size:75% position:38%
And I give being
Helen Keller five stars.

